caption: Very yum! Great place, great service! Vegan curry cauliflower, Waylay sliders, Waylay dumplings, and lamb meatballs. Also an Albino white wine.

We had the pleasure of enjoying Senia's tasting menu last night and we thoroughly enjoyed it. The dishes were nicely paced, sized and stunning on the plate. We loved most if not all of the dishes, especially the hay charred steak, gnocchi and the septagon. The frozen kumquat dish, not currently on the menu, was a such a nice treat - a great palate cleanser. The wine pairing was impeccable. The sommelier did a great job pinning the right libation with the associated tasting notes in each dish. The service overall was excellent and it was fun to see the kitchen in action. I would highly recommend Senia as great fine dining destination.

Typically not a fan of fine dining fixed course menus, but having heard about this from multiple friends and food critics, my wife and I went to try it out.  Since we were only in Honolulu for a few days, we weren’t able to get a reservation for dinner and opted to go there for lunch.  We both ordered their 3 course meals eirh the following items below: - Squash salad - Chopped salad - Confit  duck leg - Charred cabbage - Senia cookie  Wow!! It felt like there was a party in my mouth as each dish had a great distinct flavor. The Chopped Salad had a variety of greens, Salami, Avacados, garbanzo. Even though I’m not a big veggie person, the Charred cabbage was wilding beyond my expectations. HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT.  (Squash salad was the disappointment and would skip that)  The service itself was amazing as what you would expect with a fine dining establishment.  For parking, the closest parking garage is the public garage on Maunakea st & king st. No Validation.  Overall, while this place is known for their Omakase dinner menu, their lunch offering is great as well.

The entire menu is playful and beautiful. I could go on and on about each dish, but the only way to experience this menu is to be present. Smell it, see it, feel the textures, experience all five senses on a plate. The service rivals the top restaurants in the world and I cannot reccomend this restaurant any more.

Delicious food and the perfect setting for an upscale dinner to complete a night out.  Each dish was beautifully served!

I definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone who wants fantastic food with no concern of price and tastebuds that desire high-end prepared dishes. FANTASTIC!!

My wife and I had dinner for our 35th wedding anniversary here.  We had flown in to the islands from the mainland and were hoping to find a nice restaurant to have dinner. Senia was suggested by a relative and it was amazing.  This gem has an open kitchen where you can watch these talented people put together a meal unlike you have ever had.  The shared dishes are three or four bite per person exquisite dishes.  Ordering three or four dishes for the two of us was perfect.  The waitstaff never bothers you but they always know exactly when to place the next dish or take away the last empty plating.  They are prepared to answer any and all questions and you can tell that they are as pleased to serve there as the chefs are to be culinary artists and we were to partake of one of our all time favorite meals.  If you miss this one you need to return to the islands to make it a must.

I cant say enough good things about Senia. This was by far the highlight of my recent trip to Hawaii and one of the best meals I have ever had. My family and I had the pleasure of sitting at the chef's counter and we got to watch the kitchen work as we enjoyed our meal. The food is made to be shared which is great because you can try more dishes (they all were fantastic). The staff here was extremely friendly and knowledgeable, they all made us feel very comfortable. The restaurant itself is beautifully decorated, yet feels relaxed and not stuffy at all.  We also had the pleasure of meeting and talking with Chef Anthony Rush who was very kind and made for an unforgettable night.  Do yourself a favor and eat here as soon as you can. I know my wife and I already want to go back to Honolulu for the single purpose of enjoying another night at Senia.

The most amazing flavors and textures in a dish I've ever had combined with the hands-down best service we've ever had and I will continue to recommend this restaurant to everyone I know. I wish I could give them more stars.  First, quick shout out to our server, Martin. He was fun and bright and gave us recommendations on his favorite dishes (most of which we tried and he has my utmost trust from now on).  We started off with the ahi brioche which is not a menu item, but is apparently popular on their social media. It is AMAZING. Its ahi and an avocado on a homemade brioche and it explodes with flavor in your mouth. Absolutely incredible and you must try this if they have it.  The burrata was recommended to us by Martin and I wasnt sure if i would like it at first, but Im happy to say that I was so wrong. Saltiness from the goopy melty cheese, sweetness from the raisin puree and the truffle honey all over crunchy bread? That's hard to beat. I found myself enjoying it more and more with every single bite.  The charred cabbage is one of their signature dishes and very popular across social media. While this was also incredibly delicious for being a chunk of cabbage (make sure to drag it across as much of the sauce as you can), it was not my personal favorite.  Maine Sea Scallops. Incredible. They're soft on the inside. Crunchy on the tops and with the sauce and all of the accoutrements in one spoonful, it'll blow your mind.  Casoncelli with escargo and burgundy truffle shavings. This was one of my favorite pasta dishes of all time and definitely one of my favorites here. The pasta is cooked perfectly and the potatoes inside are delicious. This was my first foray into escargot and it was very very good. Everything sits in truffle and bacon oil and its a very rich dish overall.  The souffle cheesecake with the lilikoi marshmallows and the lime-avocado (its amazing) sorbet just all melts before it can hit your stomach. It's impossibly light.  The Freddie cocktail with the massive block of blood orange ice was so good. Definitely give that a shot.  Parking is found in the municipal lot in Marin Tower on Smith Street. It tops out at $3 so its quite reasonable.

Senia is a great choice for inventive fine dining in an environment that is casual and fun... And won't break your bank. We ordered a starter, 3 shared plates, a side, and a dessert for under $90 for two people. Great value for food from chefs who honed their craft at Per Se.  The luau pig croquettes were outstanding. We originally wanted to sit at the Chef's Counter for Senia's tasting menu, but having to pre-pay with a no cancellation/changes policy for my group of four didn't seem like a good bet to me so we opted for their dining room.  I love the restaurant's space with built in booths along the mixed decor walls and the simple neutral color palette.  It's pretty, modern, and sophisticated.  I like that it's not stuffy so while it's an ideal venue for a date night, it's equally a great choice for an any-night dinner out...except Sunday night.  They are closed.  We were eager to order a bottle of wine, but the wine director suggested we look over the menu and decide what we would be ordering first.  After we decided on the oysters, poke crackers, salmon, kampachi, pork belly, foie gras, and bone marrow custard we asked for his recommendation on a nice pinot noir.  Both the wine and the food were excellent.  My favorites were the poke crackers, bone marrow custard, and kampachi.  We ended our meal with the sticky toffee cake and some Kona coffee from Kona Coffee Purveyors (my fave!).  I admit if you give me good wine and company I'll have a good time, but I sincerely enjoyed my experience at Senia.  The food is original and the service was warm.  I left wanting to shout from the rooftops for everyone to, "Dine at Senia!  You will love it!!!"  Instead, I settled with a facebook post and plans to take my husband.  What the heck; yolo.
